## Scope

This summarizes the npm package **[argsbarg](https://www.npmjs.com/package/argsbarg)** (`"name": "argsbarg"`), aligned with the **`bun-argsbarg/`** symlink (→ `../bun-argsbarg`). That tree is **reference-only** — **do not edit**; see `docs/architecture.md`.

Authoritative docs: **`bun-argsbarg/readme.md`**. Public barrel: **`bun-argsbarg/src/index.ts`** (re-exports from `context.ts`, `runtime.ts`, `types.ts`).

## Mental model

- **Schema-first:** you build a tree of **`CliCommand`** objects (`key`, `description`, `options`, `positionals`, nested **`commands`**, leaf **`handler`**).
- **`cliRun(root, argv?)`** validates the tree, parses argv (default **`process.argv.slice(2)`**), prints help/errors or runs **`completion`**, invokes the matched leaf handler, then **`process.exit`** (never returns a usable value to callers — typed **`Promise<never>`**).
- **Bun-oriented**, no third-party runtime deps in the library itself; **ink-cli-demo** depends on **`argsbarg`** from npm — do not import from **`bun-argsbarg/`** in app code.

## Program root (`CliCommand` passed to `cliRun`)

- **`key`** — binary / app name (help, completions).
- **`commands`** — top-level subcommands; **`options`** — global flags.
- **Root must not** set **`handler`** or **`positionals`** (validated at startup).
- **`fallbackCommand`** + **`fallbackMode`** — only on the **root**, for default routing when argv omits or mismatches a subcommand (see table below).

## Option and positional model

- **`CliOption`:** `name`, `description`, **`kind`:** **`CliOptionKind.Presence` | `String` | `Number`**, optional **`shortName`** (single letter for **`-x`**).
- Bundled shorts (**`-abc`**) supported for presence flags.
- **`CliPositional`:** ordered slots with `name`, `description`, `kind`, optional **`argMin`** / **`argMax`** (`argMax: 0` = varargs tail; must be last). Help label rules are summarized in **`bun-argsbarg/readme.md`** (tables for `<n>`, `[n]`, etc.).

## `CliFallbackMode` (root only)

| Mode | Empty argv | Unknown first token |
|------|------------|---------------------|
| **`MissingOnly`** | default command | error |
| **`MissingOrUnknown`** | default command | default command (token fed into default) |
| **`UnknownOnly`** | root help (exit 1) | default command |

With **`MissingOrUnknown`** / **`UnknownOnly`**, unrecognized **root** flags can stop root-flag parsing; remainder goes to the default command (see readme).

## `CliContext` (leaf handlers)

| API | Role |
|-----|------|
| **`hasFlag(name)`** | Presence option set (including implicit `"1"`). |
| **`stringOpt(name)`** | `string \| undefined`. |
| **`numberOpt(name)`** | Strict double string → **`number \| null`**. |
| **`typedOpt<T>(name, parse)`** | Custom parse; **`T \| null`** on failure. |
| **`args`** | Positional words in order (`string[]`). |
| **`commandPath`**, **`appName`**, **`schema`** | Routing and merged root schema (e.g. for help). |

Some readme examples use **`ctx.flag`**; the implementation in **`CliContext`** is **`hasFlag`** — prefer **`hasFlag`** unless a future export adds an alias.

## Runtime exports (`src/index.ts`)

| Symbol | Role |
|--------|------|
| **`cliRun(root, argv?)`** | Validate, parse, dispatch, **`process.exit`**. |
| **`cliErrWithHelp(ctx, msg)`** | Stderr error line + scoped help, exit **1**. |
| **`CliCommand`**, **`CliOption`**, **`CliPositional`**, **`CliHandler`** | Schema types. |
| **`CliOptionKind`**, **`CliFallbackMode`** | Enums. |
| **`CliSchemaValidationError`** | Invalid static schema. |
| **`CliContext`** | Handler context class. |

## Built-ins (injected by `cliRun`)

- **`-h` / `--help`** at any routing depth (scoped help; exit code depends on implicit vs explicit help — see readme / runtime).
- **`completion bash`** and **`completion zsh`** — print completion scripts to stdout.
- Do **not** declare a user command whose **`key`** is **`completion`** at the root — reserved.

## When to open `./bun-argsbarg`

Use **`bun-argsbarg/readme.md`** for exit codes, completion install snippets, and edge cases. Open **`bun-argsbarg/src/*.ts`** (e.g. **`parse.ts`**, **`validate.ts`**) for parse/validation details beyond this sheet.
